> This Classic New York Style Hot Dogs is a crowd pleaser and is one to get the family round the dinner table for. Super simple to make, and easily customised to suit the kids too.

Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide chips (no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @olive oil{} and sprinkle over the @Central American Style Spice Mix{1} (add less if you'd prefer things milder). Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

While the chips cook, in a #medium bowl{}, combine the @cider vinegar{15%ml}, @sugar{1/2%tsp} and @olive oil{1%tbsp}(for the dressing) and half the @wholegrain mustard{25%g}.

Add the @coleslaw mix{120%g} to the dressing and toss to combine. Taste and season with @salt{} and @black pepper{} if needed, then set aside.

Pop the @British Hickory Smoked Sausages{2} onto another baking tray and bake on the middle shelf until golden brown and cooked through, ~{20-25%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw sausages. They're cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium heat. Once hot, add the onion, season with @salt{}, @black pepper{} and a pinch of @sugar{pinch}. Fry, stirring occasionally, until golden, ~{8-10%minutes}.

A few mins before everything's cooked, slice the @brioche hot dog buns{2} down through the middle (but not all the way through) and put them into the oven to warm, ~{2-3%minutes}.

When everything's ready, transfer the warmed buns to your plates. Spread the remaining mustard inside each bun, for anyone who wants it.

Add a sausage to each brioche bun, then top with the fried onions. Drizzle over the @tomato ketchup{2%tbsp}.

Serve the spiced chips and slaw alongside.

Enjoy!